1 A taxpayer must provide the documentation required under this subsection to the Department
2 on or before March 1, 2016, to verify that the taxpayer meets the minimum percentage of incurred
3 costs and partial construction required to be eligible for the sunset extension:
4 (1) A written certification signed by the taxpayer that, prior to January 1, 2016, at
5 least the minimum percentage of the physical construction of the project was
6 completed and that at least the minimum percentage of the total cost of the
7 project was incurred.
8 (2) A notarized copy of a written report prepared by an independent engineer duly
9 licensed in the State of North Carolina with expertise in the design and
10 construction of installations of renewable energy property stating that at least
11 the minimum percentage of the physical construction of the project was
12 completed prior to January 1, 2016.
13 (3) A notarized copy of a written report prepared by a certified public accountant
14 duly licensed to practice in the State of North Carolina with expertise in
15 accounting for and taxation of renewable energy property and that was
16 prepared in accordance with AT Section 201 of the American Institute of
17 Certified Public Accountants Standards for Agreed-Upon Procedures
18 Engagements stating that the minimum percentage of the total cost of the
19 project was paid or incurred as determined under Section 461 and other
20 relevant sections of the Code prior to January 1, 2016."
21 SECTION 2. This act is effective for taxable years beginning on or after January 1,
22 2025.
